CROP IMAGES REFERENCE GUIDE
===========================

Place crop images in this folder with the following filenames:

CEREALS & GRAINS:
- rice.jpg
- maize.jpg

LEGUMES & PULSES:
- chickpea.jpg
- kidneybeans.jpg
- pigeonpeas.jpg
- mothbeans.jpg
- mungbean.jpg
- blackgram.jpg
- lentil.jpg

FRUITS:
- pomegranate.jpg
- banana.jpg
- mango.jpg
- grapes.jpg
- watermelon.jpg
- muskmelon.jpg
- apple.jpg
- orange.jpg
- papaya.jpg
- coconut.jpg

CASH CROPS:
- cotton.jpg
- jute.jpg
- coffee.jpg

IMAGE REQUIREMENTS:
- Format: JPG or PNG (update extension in App.py if using PNG)
- Recommended size: 300x300 pixels or larger
- The images will be displayed at 300x300px with object-fit: cover

HOW TO ADD IMAGES:
1. Download or find images for each crop
2. Save them with the exact filenames listed above
3. Place them in this 'crops' folder
4. The Flask app will automatically display the corresponding image based on the prediction result

Note: If an image is missing, a placeholder message will be shown.
